President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his administration. Lane Genatowski of New York will be appointed as the Director of the Advanced Research Projects Agency-Energy at the Department of Energy. Genatowski has a background in energy investment banking and has previously worked at JP Morgan Chase, Kidder, Peabody, Bank of America, and Wells Fargo. He earned a bachelor's degree from the City University of New York and a J.D. from Fordham University School of Law.

David Hale of New Jersey will be appointed as an Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs. Hale is currently the Ambassador to the Islamic Republic of Pakistan and has previously served as the Ambassador to the Republic of Lebanon and the Ambassador to Jordan. He has also held various positions in the State Department, including Special Envoy for Middle East Peace and Deputy Assistant Secretary of State.

Bryan Jarrett of California will be appointed as an Assistant Secretary of Labor for Policy. Jarrett is currently the Acting Administrator of the Wage and Hour Division at the Department of Labor. He has previously worked as an attorney at Jones Day and Morgan, Lewis & Bockius, and clerked at the United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit. Jarrett graduated with honors from Brigham Young University and received his J.D. from Stanford Law School.